1) DESCRIPTION
--------------
pubmex.py is a script to get a fancy paper title based on given DOI or PMID.
Format of the title:
	a first author . a last author - (title("dotted") or your customed title) . PMID . journal . year . pdf
Using xclip pubmex.py automatically copy the title to the clipboard. Just type Ctrl+V or paste it somewhere else.

2) INSTALLATION
--------------

2a) LINUX
--------------

unzip & run it :-)
	- xclip (http://sourceforge.net/projects/xclip/)

2b) WINDOWS
--------------

Install:
	- http://www.python.org/ftp/python/2.6.4/python-2.6.4.msi
	- http://biopython.org/DIST/biopython-1.53.win32-py2.6.exe


3) DEPENDENCIES
--------------
pubmex.py requiers:
	- python 2.6 (http://www.python.org/)
	- biopython (http://biopython.org/wiki/Main_Page)


4) EXAMPLES
--------------

magnus@debian:~/workspace/pubmex$ python pubmex.py -h
Usage: pubmex.py [options] id

 examples: pubmex.py -p 17123955, pumex.py -d 10.1038/embor.2008.212

Options:
  --version             show program's version number and exit
  -h, --help            show this help message and exit
  -p PUBMED_ID, --pubmed_id=PUBMED_ID
                        pass PMID of the paper
  -t CUSTOMED_TITLE, --customed_title=CUSTOMED_TITLE
                        pass your title for a pdf in a format 'RNA, structure'
  -d DOI, --doi=DOI     pass DOI of the paper
  -r, --reference       reference format


magnus@debian:~/workspace/pubmex$ python pubmex.py -p 17123955
Kim.Carthew-Conversion.of.pre-RISC.to.holo-RISC.by.Ago2.during.assembly.of.RNAi.complexes.-17123955.RNA.2007.pdf

magnus@debian:~/workspace/pubmex$ python pubmex.py -p 17123955 -r
Kim K, Lee YS, Carthew RW Conversion of pre-RISC to holo-RISC by Ago2 during assembly of RNAi complexes. RNA 2007 Jan;13(1):22-9

magnus@debian:~/workspace/pubmex$ python pubmex.py -p 17123955 -t titile.i.want.to.give
Kim.Carthew-titile.i.want.to.give-17123955.RNA.2007.pdf

magnus@debian:~/workspace/pubmex$ python pubmex.py -p 17123955 -t 'my own title'
Kim.Carthew-my.own.title-17123955.RNA.2007.pdf

magnus@debian:~/workspace/pubmex$ python pubmex.py -d 10.1038/embor.2008.212
Kelley.Scott-The.evolution.of.biology.A.shift.towards.the.engineering.of.prediction-generating.tools.and.away.from.traditional.research.practice-19008917.EMBO.REP.2008.pdf

5) BUGS
--------------
pubmex.py might have still problem if it has to parse title of authors with characters like ółą and so on.

